SUMMARY:🌳☕ ST. CLAIR WEST VILLAGE WALK\, WYCHWOOD PARK & COFFEE ☕🌳
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Movies & Social Group - Celebrating 14 Years!\n🌳☕ **ST. CLAIR WEST VILLAGE WALK\, WYCHWOOD PARK & COFFEE** ☕🌳\n\nHidden Streets\, Storybook Homes & A Cozy Café Finish\nSome parts of Toronto feel like you’ve accidentally stepped into another world.\n\nJoin us for a relaxed social walk through **St. Clair West**\, leading into the quietly tucked-away and exclusive **Wychwood Park** — one of the city’s most unique residential enclaves.\n\nWychwood Park is private\, residential\, and unlike anywhere else in Toronto. The homes are all architecturally distinct — no cookie-cutter builds here — and living there involves a waiting list\, a board approval process\, and community guidelines that preserve its character. It feels almost village-like… peaceful\, artistic\, and slightly secret.\nThis is not a formal historical tour.\nIt’s a social walk with beautiful surroundings and good conversation.\n\n👉 **Don’t forget to join our WhatsApp group** – [CLICK HERE!](https://chat.whatsapp.com/H59mSCbsAi018gYANrKAnc?mode=ac_t)\n\n***\n\n🚶‍♂️ **What We’ll Do**\n\nWe’ll begin by walking west along St. Clair\, enjoying the neighbourhood energy before heading into **Wychwood Park** for a gentle wander through its winding streets.\n\nWe’ll begin by walking west along St. Clair\, enjoying the neighbourhood energy before heading into Wychwood Park for a gentle wander through its winding streets.\nAfterward\, we’ll make a short stop at **Artscape Wychwood Barns** to peek into the market space\, next we make a quick stop at Mr. Binz where everything starts at $25 and after we will head to **Bakery Garden Cafe** for a warm drink and time to sit\, chat\, and connect.\nSometimes the best part of the walk is the pause at the end. ☕\nWe’ll eventually make our way back toward St. Clair Subway Station.\nYou’re welcome to leave at any time.\n\n***\n\n❄️ **Weather & Expectations**\n\nPlease do not sign up if you’re not ready to walk in real winter conditions. This event will happen in snow\, cold\, or typical Toronto winter weather.\n\nThe only exception: if temperatures reach -20°C\, the event will be canceled.\n\nBundle up. Dress properly. This is a winter walk.\nAlso — this is NOT a historical tour. I’ll share context casually\, but the focus is social connection and enjoying the neighbourhood.\n\n***\n\n🧢 Meetup Details\n📍 Meetup Location: Outside the station by McDonald’s\n🫎 I’ll be wearing my Moose Hat\n⏰ Meetup Time: 11:00 AM\nI will only wait 5 minutes.\nEarly is on time.\nOn time is late.\nWe will leave promptly\, and I won’t be able to spend time trying to track people down — thank you for respecting everyone’s time.\n\n***\n\n🎟️ **Meetup Fee:** $5 cash in person **or** e-transfer to\n📧 \\*\\*[mathewmaclean@hotmail.com**](http://mathewmaclean@hotmail.com%2A%2A/)\nThis fee helps support the group and allows us to keep hosting events like this. Thank you for supporting community! 💖\n\n***\n\n🎒 What to Bring\n\n* Water or a warm drink\n* Good walking shoes\n* A small snack\n* Warm clothing (boots\, hat\, gloves — layers!)\n* Mask (if you prefer for indoor stops)\n\nPlease also use the washroom before arriving\, as stops are limited.\n\n***\n\n📚 Learn More\nInterested in reading more about Wychwood Park before we go [Click Here](https://www.thestar.com/news/insight/2012/12/21/inside_the_weird_world_of_wychwood_park.html)?\n\n🌈 Who Is This For?\nThis group is open to anyone who wants to be social and make friends — whether single or not.\nWe also host:\n🎬 Movies\n🚶 Walks & hikes\n🎭 Arts & culture outings\n🍽️ Restaurant gatherings\nThere’s always something happening.\n\n***\n\nREMEMBER: You’re welcome to just show up on the day if you’re unsure about your schedule.\nAnd as always\, sometimes plans shift and events may need to be canceled — please keep an eye on updates.\n\n***\n\n👤 Organizer: Mathew\nQuestions? Post on the event wall or email\n📧 torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com\n\nCome for the hidden streets. Stay for the cozy coffee.\nLeave feeling like you discovered a pocket of the city most people never see.\nThere’s something special about wandering somewhere that feels quietly exclusive — especially when you’re not wandering alone. 🌳✨
